**Problem Statement**

A small automobile spare parts shop sells spare parts for a variety of vehicles across several makes and models. Each spare part may be manufactured by multiple small-scale industries, making it necessary to manage a large inventory of diverse items efficiently.

To streamline sales operations and supply ordering, the shop owner has commissioned the development of the Motor Part Shop Software (MPSS). This software will address the key requirements and challenges associated with managing the inventory and sales of motor parts.

The shop deals with a vast number of motor parts, catering to various vehicle types and manufacturers. These parts vary in size—some are very small, while others are relatively large. To organize the physical storage, the shop maintains parts in wall-mounted and numbered racks.

Inspired by the "Just-In-Time (JIT)" inventory philosophy, the shop owner aims to minimize inventory overheads. As a result, the shop keeps only a reasonable quantity of each item in stock. A crucial challenge faced by the shop is ensuring timely reordering of items when their stock levels fall below a certain threshold.

The MPSS must automatically track sales data and compute the average weekly sales for each part. Based on this average, the system should determine a threshold stock value that would allow sales to continue for approximately one week without replenishment.

At the end of each day, the shop owner will request the system to generate a procurement report. This report must include:

The part number

The quantity required to replenish the stock

The address of the vendor who supplies the part

Additionally, the software must:

Compute and report the daily revenue generated from sales

At the end of each month, generate a graphical report showing the daily sales figures for that month

This system aims to improve the efficiency and accuracy of the inventory management and ordering process, ultimately enhancing the business performance and customer satisfaction of the spare parts shop.

**Introduction**

The Motor Part Shop Software (MPSS) is a comprehensive web-based solution to digitize and automate daily operations of a motor parts retail shop. With increasing demands, numerous part types, and suppliers, managing inventory and processing sales manually becomes inefficient and error-prone. MPSS facilitates streamlined, user-role-based interaction with real-time data visibility.
